13/10/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The General Prosecution Offices of Albania and Kosovo will work closely in the future by sharing information, following Tuesday's (October 12th) signing of a memorandum on co-operation. Albanian General Prosecutor Ina Rama and Kosovo counterpart Ismet Kabashi also discussed reforms and developments in their countries' judiciaries. Rama stressed the positive effects that the anti-mafia law has had in fighting organised crime. Kabashi briefed her about reforms and close co-operation with EULEX. They agreed that sharing information and evidence will help bring criminals to justice. (Balkan Web, Telegrafi, Klan, Alsat - 12/10/10)
